File: The aftermath of a vigilante attack in Zandspruit. (eNCA) JOHANNESBURG - The case involving suspects in the Zandspruit vigilante attack has been postponed to next month for bail application. Six suspects, including a woman, appeared in the Roodepoort Magistrate's Court on Monday. They are facing murder, attempted murder, and kidnapping charges. READ: Vigilante Attack | 6 Zandspruit accused in court Last week, a group of young men, accused of terrorising the community, was taken to a local sports ground and beaten up by an angry mob. The young men were doused with petrol and set alight. Four died on the scene and four died later in hospital. In court, the media was not allowed to film or photograph the suspects for legal and investigative reasons.